text: Thomas Parsonage (13 November 1910 - 3 February 1951) was an Australian cricketer. He played one first-class match for New South Wales in 1932/33. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1910 births Category:1951 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Sydney
